Overview:

There are 4 tasks:

Demux: Read incoming transport packet from CFifoIn.
       If PID indicates this is the stream to be bit reduced, parse the payload
           and extract the PES header, if any, and put it in the PES queue.
           Dump the PES payload into one of the inBuf.
       If PID indicates this is one of the selected stream not to be bit
           reduced, then copy the entire transport packet into the
           corresponding PID queue.
       If PID is not selected, simply discard the packet.

BitShaper: Read video elementary stream data from one of the InBuf.
       At the bigining of a picture, attach the corresponding PES header in
       the PES queue to the output buffer.
       Pass all headers and extension up to and including the picture layer
       to the output buffer.
       Modify macroblock layer if necessary, decode and re-encode DCT data
       and send them to the output buffer.

Packetizer: Read video PES data from output buffer and hand them to mux.


Important data structures/buffers and their content:

Input CFIFO: incoming transport packets.  256 TPs
PID queues: transport packets of selected PIDs (not to be bit reduced)
PES queues: PES headers of PID to be bit reduced
Input buffes (2): video elementary stream data.  4 KB each
Output buffers: video PES data.  4 KB?
Output CFIFO: transport packets of all selected PIDs.  256 TPs



cfifo.h, cfifo.c: CFIFO
The CFIFO size is set to 256 transport packets (for both input and output FIFO).
Semaphores are used for CFIFO.


pidbuf.h, pidbuf.c: PID buffer
PID buffers are used to hold the entire transport packets of the selected PIDs.
PID Buffers (actually it is the buffers for the transport packets):
  PidQueHandle contains information of all PID Queues available
  PidQue is the queue for one PID
  PidBuf is a buffer which holds one transport packet.
  PidFreeBufHandle is the structure of linked list for the unused PidBufs.


pes.h, pes.c: PES Handling
Buffers are used to hold the PES headers of the selected PID for rate reduction.
Structures: PesQueHandle (freeQue, fullQue and freeSema)
	    PesElem (contains PES header info: ptrs to PES header,
                     PES header size, and picture id which owns this PES header)

NOTE:
  It seems to me that the code assumes that there is one PES header per frame.
  There is no indication to where the PES header should be inserted, but always
  assuming to be at the beginning of a picture.


tp.c: transport packet operations
findPayload()
tpParse()
tpAFParse(): adaptation field
tpAFGetPCR()
readPesHdr()
readMorePesHdr()
dumpPayload()

demux.c: Demux task
demux()


buf.h, buf.c: input and output buffer operations
Structure: InBuf (data buffer pointer, read/write pointers, sema)

Output buffer are defined as distributed global variables: outBuf(Uint32*)
  bitPosOutRead, bitPosOutWrite, outBufSemBitReduce, outBufSemMux

Note:
  - outBuf is also defined here, and is just a Uint32*



videoes.c

The two functions buf_inputbits() and buf_outputbits() are called to input
and output bits.

getMBs() performs all slice and macroblock level processing.
getmpg2intrablock() and getmpg2interblock() are called to decode a DCT block.
encodeMBData() are then called to re-encode the DCT data.

_extU(), _clrU(), _setU() are C6X compiler supported macros which translate
directly into C6X instructions.
